section.section:
Notwithstanding paragraphs (2) and (3) of this subsection, for a loan that is to be secured by residential real property:
A licensee may solicit and accept an application for a loan:
By mail;
By telephone or other electronic means; or
At any location requested by the prospective borrower;
Except as provided in subparagraph (iii) of this paragraph, the loan closing shall be conducted at:
The lender's licensed location;
The office of an attorney representing the licensee, the borrower, the title company, or title insurer in connection with the loan; or
The office of the title insurer or title agency performing closing services in connection with the loan; and
A licensee may conduct the loan closing at another location at the written request of the borrower or the borrower's designee to accommodate the borrower because of the borrower's sickness.
